<p>A r&eacute;sum&eacute; is a  sample of your writing skills and should represent your best work.                                                         Thus, it should  be professional: clear, concise, consistent, error-free, and up-to-date.</p>
<p>The following  guidelines are meant to assist you in presenting yourself professionally                                                         to potential  employers and/or experience providers and to help you show them how                                                         you meet their  needs.</p>
<p>Many different  ideas exist on the proper procedure and style for creating a r&eacute;sum&eacute;.                                                         Some people  insist on one thing, some on another.</p>
<p>So who's right? <em>Your audience</em>.</p>
<p>Though the style  you use and the information you include in a r&eacute;sum&eacute; is ultimately                                                         yours, the most  important thing you can do, in all phases of the job search, is                                                         to know the  needs of your audience and tailor your r&eacute;sum&eacute; accordingly.</p>
<ul>
<li>To learn more about how to research your audience, utilize the <a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Advising/careerprep/KnowYourAudienceGuide.pdf" title="Know Your Audience Guide" target="_blank">Know Your Audience (KYA) Guide.</a></li>
<li>To understand  the process of tailoring your r&eacute;sum&eacute; and cover letter to your audience,                                                         read the <a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Advising/tailor_coverletter.pdf" title="Tailoring your Cover Letter and Resume PDF" target="_blank"> Tailoring Your Cover Letter and R&eacute;sum&eacute;</a> PDF                                                         document.</li>
<li>For help in starting from scratch, utilize Optimal R&eacute;sum&eacute;. Log in to your my.byui.edu account, select the Services tab, then Optimal R&eacute;sum&eacute;. </li>
<li><a href="http://stream.byui.edu/internships/resume_review.wmv" target="blank">R&eacute;sum&eacute;                                                             Writing Seminar - Christopher Galbraith</a> (1 hour video)</li>
</ul>
